posts.author: votedforthe45th
posts.title: 'No US Citizens': Meet the IT Firms Discriminating Against Americans

link_metadata.description: The job post for LanceSoft, an IT staffing firm committed to "diversity, equality, and inclusivity," began innocently enough. The $60-per-hour role would be based in Santa Clara, Calif., focus on "technical support," and entail a 3-10 p.m. shift. Posted on Nvoids, an IT jobs aggregator, the ad described LanceSoft as an equal opportunity employer and said that the firm, one of the largest staffing agencies in the country, strives "to be as diverse as the clients and employees we partner with." "We embrace people of any race, ethnicity, national origin, religion, gender identity, and sexual orientation," the Nov. 25 post read. This particular job, however, would not be open to a very large group of people: citizens of the United States.
